The Duke of Sussex preached the importance of "peak mental fitness" in a campaign video promoting £3.8million Silicon Valley start-up Better Up. He urged people to focus on "flexing their minds" rather than "fixing them". But not everyone agreed, Twitter user @ospenstein asked: "What would he know about that?" @pattietierney said: "Yet another subject about which he knows nothing" with @talulahbluebell agreeing, adding: "Exactly...insulting to qualified graduates in the field." FOLLOW BELOW FOR MORE... 